MerbInterface
=============

A slice of dynamic markup and style for the Merb framework.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation
============

1.) In file "config/init.rb", add:

dependency 'merb-interface'

2.) In file "config/rack.rb", add:

use Merb::Rack::Static, MerbInterface.dir_for(:public)

3.) In file "config/router.rb", add:

r.add_slice(:MerbInterface, :default_routes => false, :path => '')

4.) In file "app/views/layout/application.html.erb", add within <head></head>:

<%= mi_assets %>

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example View
============

<%= mi_row do%>
  <%= mi_column do %>
    <%= mi_title('MerbInterface') %>
  	<%= mi_paragraph do %>MerbInterface is an HTML/CSS pattern Merb Slice. MerbInterface's professionally designed components may be mixed within your Merb application's views.<% end =%>
    <%= mi_link('Project Overview', :url => 'http://uipoet.lighthouseapp.com/projects/14717-merb-interface/overview') %>
    <%= mi_link('Source Code', :url => 'http://github.com/uipoet/merb-interface/tree/master') %>
    <%= mi_title('MerbFlickr') %>
  	<%= mi_paragraph do %>MerbFlickr is a Flickr photo gallery Merb Slice. It leverages the components of MerbInterface. With supplying only a Flickr API key, Shared Secret, and User ID, you get a polished working gallery of Flickr Sets that's ready to be customized.<% end =%>
    <%= mi_link('Project Overview', :url => 'http://uipoet.lighthouseapp.com/projects/14716-merb-flickr/overview') %>
    <%= mi_link('Source Code', :url => 'http://github.com/uipoet/merb-flickr/tree/master') %>
  <% end =%>
  <%= mi_column do %>
    <%= mi_tray do %>
      <%= mi_merb %>
    	<%= mi_paragraph do %><%= mi_link('Ruby', :url => 'http://www.ruby-lang.org/') %> is a dynamic, open source programming language with a focus on simplicity and productivity. It has an elegant syntax that is natural to read and easy to write.<% end =%>
    	<%= mi_paragraph do %>Ruby programs and libraries are easily distributed and installed as Gems. <%= mi_link('RubyGems', :url => 'http://www.rubygems.org/') %> is the premier ruby packaging system. <% end =%>
    	<%= mi_paragraph do %><%= mi_link('Merb', :url => 'http://www.merbivore.com/') %> is a Ruby model, view, controller framework for creating web applications.<% end =%>
    	<%= mi_paragraph do %>Merb is agnostic about which object-relational mapping, JavaScript library, or template language you decide to use. Easily installed as a Gem, Merb supports plugins that are also installed as Gems. Optionally add whichever functionality you need.<% end =%>
    	<%= mi_paragraph do %>Merb-Slices is a Merb plugin for using application 'Slices'. A Slice is just like a regular Merb MVC application, both in functionality as well as in structure.<% end =%>
    <% end =%>
  <% end =%>
<% end =%>

